aren, nicht wesentlich von anderen Frauen unterscheiden. Die rassistische Produktion von Andersheit wird so als eine soziale Praxis und strukturelle Dimension moderner Gesellschaften erkennbar.  aThe stereotypical stigmatization of the headscarf is a practice of anti-muslim racism. On the basis of qualitative interview data, Florian Kreutzer reveals daily practices of racist discrimination, of `doing race' and racial othering - and likewise the practices and possibilities of undoing race, of crossing out, undermining, overcoming and undoing the racist production of alterity. The stories about veiled women make it clear that in the ways that they combine family and work, that they cannot be essentially distinguished from other women. The racist production of alterity becomes recognizable as a social practice and structural dimension of modern societies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aHijab (Islamic clothing) 0aHijab (Islamic clothing). 0aIslamophobiazGermany. 0aMass mediaxSocial aspects. 0aMuslim womenzGermany. 0aOnline social networksxCase studies. 0aReligion and statezGermany. 4aArbeits- und Industriesoziologie. 4aGender Studies. 4aGeschlecht. 4aIntegration. 4aIslam. 4aIslamwissenschaft. 4aKopftuch. 4aMigration. 4aRassismus. 4aStigma. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Jewish Studies.2bisacsh  aGender Studies.  aIntegration.  aIslam.  aIslamic Studies.  aMigration.  aRacism.  aSociology of Work and Industry.  aStigma.  aVeil.1 aDemir, Sümeyye.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theology, Relig. Studies, Jewish Studies 2015z9783110438727oZDB-23-DGF08iT